{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.37",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 37,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 37",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 37 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:1",
      "text": "At this also my heart is troubled, and moved out of its place.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:2",
      "text": "Hear thou a report by the anger of the Lord’s wrath, and a discourse shall come out of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:3",
      "text": "His dominion is under the whole heaven, and his light is at the extremities of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:4",
      "text": "After him shall be a cry with a loud voice; he shall thunder with the voice of his excellency, yet he shall not cause men to pass away, for one shall hear his voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:5",
      "text": "The Mighty One shall thunder wonderfully with his voice: for he has done great things which we knew not;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:6",
      "text": "commanding the snow, Be thou upon the earth, and the stormy rain, and the storm of the showers of his might.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:7",
      "text": "He seals up the hand of every man, that every man may know his own weakness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:8",
      "text": "And the wild beasts come in under the covert, and rest in their lair.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:9",
      "text": "Troubles come on out of the secret chambers, and cold from the mountain-tops.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:10",
      "text": "And from the breath of the Mighty One he will send frost; and he guides the water in whatever way he pleases.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:11",
      "text": "And if a cloud obscures what is precious to him, his light will disperse the cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:12",
      "text": "And he will carry round the encircling clouds by his governance, to perform their works: whatsoever he shall command them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:13",
      "text": "this has been appointed by him on the earth, whether for correction, or for his land, or if he shall find him an object for mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:14",
      "text": "Hearken to this, O Job: stand still, and be admonished of the power of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:15",
      "text": "We know that God has disposed his works, having made light out of darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:16",
      "text": "And he knows the divisions of the clouds, and the signal overthrows of the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:17",
      "text": "But thy robe is warm, and there is quiet upon the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:18",
      "text": "Wilt thou establish with him foundations for the ancient heavens? they are strong as a molten mirror.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:19",
      "text": "Wherefore teach me, what shall we say to him? and let us cease from saying much.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:20",
      "text": "Have I a book or a scribe my me, that I may stand and put man to silence?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:21",
      "text": "But the light is not visible to all: it shines afar off in the heavens, as that which is from him in the clouds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:22",
      "text": "From the north come the clouds shining like gold: in these great are the glory and honour of the Almighty;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:23",
      "text": "and we do not find another his equal in strength: as for him that judges justly, dost thou not think that he listens?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.37.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:24",
      "text": "Wherefore men shall fear him; and the wise also in heart shall fear him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
